00:24:23.160 --> 00:24:27.120
Now, in Foundry, we have a set
of evaluators that you can use.

00:24:27.120 --> 00:24:31.680
We have built-in evaluators that
help measure around quality,

00:24:31.680 --> 00:24:35.130
things like, is the intent
being adhered or not.

00:24:35.130 --> 00:24:38.010
It can help also measure
built-in evaluators around risk

00:24:38.010 --> 00:24:41.010
and safety, and also
agentic evaluators

00:24:41.010 --> 00:24:42.390
that will help you understand

00:24:42.390 --> 00:24:47.010
if the solution is actually
following across multiple terms.

00:24:47.010 --> 00:24:49.530
We also have the ability to
create custom evaluators,

00:24:49.530 --> 00:24:52.260
prompt code, and, as we
are announcing today

00:24:52.260 --> 00:24:55.360
at the conference,
rubric-based evaluators.

00:24:57.780 --> 00:25:00.510
Oh, we're announcing today,
